Claims CLAIMS  What is claimed is: 1. A system that synchronously renders a first compressed video stream, comprising: a stream receiver that receives the first compressed video stream from a first broadcast source; a metadata goncrator that inserts a first frame identifier into the first compressed video stream to generate a modified first compressed video stream; a stream transmitter that transmits the modified first compressed video stream; a control transmitter that transmits a synchronizing signal; and a plurality of display nodes that receive the modified first compressed video stream and the synchronizing signal, wherein each of the plurality of display nodes selectively presents the modified first compressed video stream as a function of the synchronizing signal. 2. The system of claim 1 , wherein the metadata generator is further configured to insert the first frame identifier between an encoded first frame and an encoded second frame of the compressed video stream, and wherein the modified compressed video stream comprises the encoded first frame and the encoded second frame. 3. The system of any of the preceding claims, wherein the first compressed video stream comprises a first presentation time stamp corresponding to the encoded first frame. 4. The system of any of the preceding claims, wherein the metadata generator is further configured to insert a second frame identifier into the compressed video stream to generate the modified compressed video stream. 5. The system of any of the preceding claims, wherein the metadata generator is further configured to generate a metadata block comprising the first frame identifier and a thumbnail into the first compressed video stream, wherein the first frame identifier corresponds to a first frame of the compressed video stream, and wherein the thumbnail is generated using at least the first frame of the compressed video stream. 6. The system of any of the preceding claims, further comprising a controller user interface configured to present the thumbnail as a visual representation of the first frame. 7. The system of any of the preceding claims, wherein the synchronizing signal comprises the first frame identifier and a time stamp. 8. The system of any of the preceding claims, wherein the synchronizing signal comprises a series of frame identifiers each paired with a different time stamp. 9. The system of any of the preceding claims, wherein the stream receiver is further configured to receive a second compressed video stream from a second broadcast source, wherein the metadata generator is further configured to insert a second frame identifier into the second compressed video stream to generate a modified second compressed video stream, wherein the transmitter is further configured to transmit the modified second compressed video stream to the plurality of display nodes, and wherein each of the plurality of display nodes is also configured to selectively present the modified second compressed video stream as a function of the synchronizing signal. 10. The system of any of the preceding claims, wherein a first frame rate of the first compressed video stream is different from a second frame rate of the second compressed video stream. 1 1. A method of synchronously rendering a compressed video stream, comprising: receiving a first compressed video stream by a stream receiving module; inserting, by a metadata generation module, a first frame identifier into the first compressed video stream to generate a modified first compressed video stream; transmitting, by a stream transmission module, the modified first compressed video stream to a plurality of display nodes; transmitting, by a control module, a synchronizing signal to the plurality of display nodes; and presenting, by each of the display nodes, a selection of the modified first compressed video stream as a function of the synchronizing signal. 12. The method of any of the preceding claims, wherein the metadata generation module is configured to insert the first frame identifier between an encoded first frame and an encoded 

 second frame of the compressed video stream, and wherein the modified compressed video stream comprises the encoded first frame and the encoded second frame. 13. The method of any of the preceding claims, wherein the first compressed video stream comprises a first presentation time stamp corresponding to the encoded first frame. 14. The method of any of the preceding claims, wherein the metadata generation module is further configured to insert a second frame identifier into the compressed video stream to generate the modified compressed video stream. 15. The method of any of the preceding claims, wherein the metadata generation module is further configured to insert a frame identifier corresponding to every encoded frame of the compressed video stream. 16. The method of any of the preceding claims, wherein the metadata generation module is further configured to generate a metadata block comprising the first frame identifier and a thumbnail into the first compressed video stream, wherein the first frame identifier corresponds to a first frame of the compressed video stream, and wherein metadata generation module is further configured to generate the thumbnail using at least the first frame of the compressed video stream. 17. The method of any of the preceding claims, further comprising presenting, via the control module, a video player user interface that presents the thumbnail as a visual representation of the first frame. 18. The method of any of the preceding claims, wherein the synchronizing signal comprises the first frame identifier and a time stamp. 19. The method of any of the preceding claims, wherein the synchronizing signal comprises a series of frame identifiers, each paired with a different time stamp. 20. The method of any of the preceding claims, further comprising: receiving, by the stream receiving module, a second compressed video stream; inserting, by the metadata generation module, a second frame identifier into the second compressed video stream to generate a modified second compressed video stream; 

 transmitting, by the stream transmission module, the modified second compressed video stream to the plurality of display computing devices; and presenting, by each of the plurality of display devices, the second modified compressed video stream as a function of the synchronizing signal.
